# deck-harness project config

Copy this file to `.claude/deck-harness.local.md` at your project root **only if** a default does not fit.
The skill reads it when a run starts; a missing file simply means every default below applies.

Format: plain `key: value` lines. Blank lines, `#` comments, and surrounding markdown prose are ignored.

```
# Directory holding a deck font family, named DeckSans-200.otf … DeckSans-900.otf.
# No font ships with this plugin. Unset = the system sans stack is used, which renders fine.
font_dir: assets/fonts

# Where finished decks are written. Project-root-relative or absolute.
output_root: output

# Where you drop source material (images, prior decks, brand guides) for asset-curator to pull from.
reference_root: reference

# Default presenter name substituted into {{PRESENTER}} when the user does not give one.
presenter:

# Where the feedback loop writes lessons.md / patterns.json / raw/.
feedback_root: feedback
```

## Keys

| Key | Required | Default | Effect |
|---|---|---|---|
| `font_dir` | no | *(unset)* | Directory of `DeckSans-{200..900}.otf`. Copied into each deck's `assets/fonts/`. Unset → system sans fallback |
| `output_root` | no | `output` | Base dir for `output/{title}/` |
| `reference_root` | no | `reference` | Project-shared source-material pool |
| `presenter` | no | *(ask the user)* | Default `{{PRESENTER}}` value |
| `feedback_root` | no | `feedback` | Base dir for the capture → promotion loop |

## Fonts

This plugin ships **no font binaries**. The deck templates declare a family called `DeckSans` at eight
weights and fall back to `-apple-system, sans-serif`, so a deck renders correctly with nothing installed.

To use a specific family, put eight weights in `font_dir` renamed to the weight scheme:

```
DeckSans-200.otf  DeckSans-300.otf  DeckSans-400.otf  DeckSans-500.otf
DeckSans-600.otf  DeckSans-700.otf  DeckSans-800.otf  DeckSans-900.otf
```

Verify the licence permits embedding and redistribution before you ship a deck that carries the files.

## Known limitation — agent auto-patching

`consolidate_feedback.py` patches repeat patterns (count >= 2) into `<project>/.claude/agents/*.md`.
When the agents are loaded from the installed plugin rather than your project, there is nothing at that
path and the script prints a warning and skips that step — `lessons.md` and `patterns.json` still
accumulate normally. To enable auto-patching, copy the agents you want to evolve into your project's
`.claude/agents/`; the project copy takes precedence and becomes the one that learns.
